@pwr617 yes, this works but its not an optimal solution as you can't exploit the multithreaded dataloader. It seems that the updated dataset property is not passed correctly when multithreading is used. I don't see an easy solution. I suppose for now I will hard code setting num_workers to 0 when multi-scale is used. Also beware, I believe darknet training does not start using multiscale until the very last few epochs.

UPDATE: I've hardcoded the change in train.py, and I'll leave this issue open until this is resolved.
